[2026-03-13T17:54:42Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013bxStK7EaAfQ5R1H5RHw6g","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report on how run status is computed in this Go project.\n\n## Comprehensive Report: Run Status Computation in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how run status is computed and managed in the Cloche system:\n\n### 1. **Domain Types for Run, Step, Result, and Status**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n- **RunState Constants** (lines 8-16):\n  - `RunStatePending` - run hasn't started\n  - `RunStateRunning` - run is executing\n  - `RunStateSucceeded` - run completed successfully\n  - `RunStateFailed` - run failed\n  - `RunStateCancelled` - run was cancelled\n\n- **Run Structure** (lines 31-48):\n  - `State`: current RunState\n  - `StepExecutions`: array of completed/executing steps\n  - `ActiveSteps`: list of currently executing step names\n  - `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: timestamps\n\n- **StepExecution Structure** (lines 18-25):\n  - `StepName`: the step identifier\n  - `Result`: the step's result name (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", \"error\")\n  - `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: execution timestamps\n  - `Logs`: output logs\n  - `GitRef`: for tracking output state\n\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `RecordStepStart()` - tracks when a step begins\n  - `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` - records step completion with result\n  - `Complete(state)` - sets final run state\n  - `Fail(msg)` - marks run as failed with error message\n\n### 2. **How Run Status is Currently Calculated/Aggregated**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe **Engine** (the workflow orchestrator) is responsible for computing the final run state based on step results and wiring/control flow. The key logic is in `Engine.Run()` (lines 83-278):\n\n**Status Computation Flow:**\n\n1. **Initial State** (line 92): Run starts as `RunStateRunning`\n\n2. **Step Execution** (lines 133-160): \n   - Steps are launched and tracked in `StepExecutions`\n   - `RecordStepStart()` adds step to active list\n   - Results flow back through channel\n\n3. **Error Handling** (lines 178-193):\n   - If a step returns an error → Run marked `RunStateFailed` immediately\n   - If step returns undeclared result → Run marked `RunStateFailed` immediately\n\n4. **Control Flow via Wiring** (lines 198-225):\n   - Step results are wired to next steps via the `Workflow.NextSteps()` method\n   - Results map to: normal steps, `domain.StepDone` (success terminal), or `domain.StepAbort` (failure terminal)\n   - Each time a target is processed:\n     - If target is `StepDone` → increment `doneCount`\n     - If target is `StepAbort` → set `aborted = true`\n     - Otherwise → launch the target step\n\n5. **Collect Conditions** (lines 227-262):\n   - Collects work similarly but can wait for multiple conditions:\n     - `CollectAll`: all conditions must be satisfied before triggering\n     - `CollectAny`: any condition triggers the target\n\n6. **Final State Determination** (lines 266-274):\n   ```go\n   if aborted || runErr != nil {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   } else if doneCount > 0 {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   } else {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n       runErr = fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: no branches reached done\", wf.Name)\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Key Insight:** A run succeeds if and only if **at least one branch reaches `domain.StepDone`**. A run fails if:\n- Any step returns an error\n- A step returns an undeclared result\n- The workflow aborts (via `StepAbort`)\n- No branch reaches `StepDone`\n\n### 3. **How \"Attempts\" Work**\n\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 69-134)\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` (line 65)\n\n**Attempt Mechanism:**\n\nAn \"attempt\" is a single execution of an agent step within a retry loop. The system supports `max_attempts` configuration per step:\n\n**Configuration:**\n```\nstep_config[\"max_attempts\"] = \"3\"  // string representation of max retries\n```\n\n**Workflow:**\n\n1. **Check Before Execution** (lines 70-78 in prompt.go):\n   - Before running an agent step, the adapter reads the attempt count from disk\n   - If `count >= max_attempts` → step returns `\"give-up\"` result (special terminal)\n   - This allows workflows to wire give-up to an abort or different path\n\n2. **Increment Counter** (line 79):\n   - `incrementAttemptCount()` writes counter to `.cloche/attempt_count/{stepName}`\n   - Each read/write is to a separate file per step (allows multiple concurrent steps)\n\n3. **Reset on Success** (lines 123-125):\n   - When a step completes with `\"success\"` result → counter is reset to 0\n   - This prevents give-up from triggering after successful fixes whose downstream tests fail unrelated\n   - Pattern: **Attempts only count consecutive failures**\n\n4. **Attempt Counter Implementation** (lines 441-473):\n   - `readAttemptCount()` - reads from `.cloche/attempt_count/{stepName}` (returns 0 if not found)\n   - `incrementAttemptCount()` - creates dir and increments counter\n   - `resetAttemptCount()` - deletes the counter file\n\n5. **Lifecycle** (agent/runner.go line 65):\n   - Entire attempt_count directory is cleared at start of each workflow run\n   - So attempts are tracked per-run, not globally\n\n**Example Workflow Pattern:**\n```\nstep code (agent, max_attempts=3):\n  success → test\n  fail → code (retry)\n  give-up → abort\n```\n\nThis creates an automatic retry loop that gives up after 3 consecutive failures.\n\n### 4. **Existing Tests for Status Computation**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine_test.go`\n\nKey tests include:\n\n1. **TestEngine_LinearWorkflow** (lines 29-50):\n   - Tests simple linear flow: build → test → done\n   - Verifies `RunStateSucceeded` when done is reached\n\n2. **TestEngine_RetryLoop** (lines 52-84):\n   - Tests retry mechanism with:\n     - code (agent) → success/fail\n     - check (script) → pass/fail\n     - fail from check loops back to code\n   - Verifies retry logic and success completion\n\n3. **TestEngine_Abort** (lines 86-105):\n   - Tests abort path: code fail → abort\n   - Verifies `RunStateFailed` when abort is reached\n\n4. **TestEngine_ContextCancellation** (lines 107-128):\n   - Tests context cancellation → `RunStateCancelled`\n\n5. **TestEngine_Fanout** (lines 130-161):\n   - Tests parallel branches all reaching done\n   - Verifies all branches execute\n\n6. **TestEngine_CollectAll** (lines 163-200):\n   - Tests collect waiting for multiple conditions\n   - Verifies merge step only triggers when both test and lint succeed\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go`\n\n1. **TestRun_Lifecycle** (lines 11-31):\n   - Tests state transitions: Pending → Running → Succeeded\n   - Verifies step recording and completion\n\n2. **TestRun_Fail** (lines 54-61):\n   - Tests failure state and error message\n\n### 5. **Additional Status Concepts**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go`\n\nThere's a separate **HealthStatus** concept for project-level health (different from Run state):\n\n- **HealthGreen**: all completed runs in window succeeded\n- **HealthRed**: all completed runs in window failed\n- **HealthYellow**: mix of passed and failed\n- **HealthBlue**: all runs in window are in-progress (pending/running)\n- **HealthGrey**: no runs provided\n\nThis is computed via `CalculateHealth()` (lines 31-76), which takes the most recent N runs and classifies them, independent of run status computation.\n\n### 6. **Status Flow Through the System**\n\n1. **Engine execution** → computes RunState based on step results\n2. **Host executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`, line 217) → maps RunState to step result:\n   - `RunStateSucceeded` → `\"success\"` step result\n   - `RunStateFailed` → `\"fail\"` step result\n3. **Host runner** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, lines 144-154) → persists final state to store\n4. **Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`, lines 197-256) → logs and broadcasts status changes\n5. **Store** (`ports.RunStore`) → persists the Run object with final State\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Run** | Tracks state, step executions, timestamps |\n| **StepExecution** | Records individual step result name |\n| **Engine** | Computes final RunState from step results + wiring |\n| **Attempts** | Per-step consecutive failure counter, resets on success |\n| **Wiring** | Maps (step, result) to next steps or terminals |\n| **StatusHandler** | Logs/broadcasts state changes |\n| **Health** | Aggregates recent runs into project-level status |\n\nThe system design is clean: **Engine is the authority on Run status computation**, while everything else either feeds data to it or consumes its output."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab5a7d2d214b2bee0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63927\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 51083</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"672a244f-d306-4bfb-8514-5ea42ce22c11","uuid":"31537428-d502-4dc3-b5c1-aa44868e7def","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore how run status is computed in this Go project. I need to understand:\n\n1. The domain types for Run, Step, Result, Status - look in internal/domain/\n2. How run status is currently calculated/aggregated from step statuses\n3. How \"attempts\" work - what constitutes an attempt\n4. Any existing tests for status computation\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/domain/, internal/ports/, and any other relevant directories. Read all relevant files completely. Pay special attention to any Status() method or ComputeStatus function, and how step results map to run status.\n\nBe very thorough - read all domain files, status-related code, and test files.","agentId":"ab5a7d2d214b2bee0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report on how run status is computed in this Go project.\n\n## Comprehensive Report: Run Status Computation in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how run status is computed and managed in the Cloche system:\n\n### 1. **Domain Types for Run, Step, Result, and Status**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n- **RunState Constants** (lines 8-16):\n  - `RunStatePending` - run hasn't started\n  - `RunStateRunning` - run is executing\n  - `RunStateSucceeded` - run completed successfully\n  - `RunStateFailed` - run failed\n  - `RunStateCancelled` - run was cancelled\n\n- **Run Structure** (lines 31-48):\n  - `State`: current RunState\n  - `StepExecutions`: array of completed/executing steps\n  - `ActiveSteps`: list of currently executing step names\n  - `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: timestamps\n\n- **StepExecution Structure** (lines 18-25):\n  - `StepName`: the step identifier\n  - `Result`: the step's result name (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", \"error\")\n  - `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: execution timestamps\n  - `Logs`: output logs\n  - `GitRef`: for tracking output state\n\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `RecordStepStart()` - tracks when a step begins\n  - `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` - records step completion with result\n  - `Complete(state)` - sets final run state\n  - `Fail(msg)` - marks run as failed with error message\n\n### 2. **How Run Status is Currently Calculated/Aggregated**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe **Engine** (the workflow orchestrator) is responsible for computing the final run state based on step results and wiring/control flow. The key logic is in `Engine.Run()` (lines 83-278):\n\n**Status Computation Flow:**\n\n1. **Initial State** (line 92): Run starts as `RunStateRunning`\n\n2. **Step Execution** (lines 133-160): \n   - Steps are launched and tracked in `StepExecutions`\n   - `RecordStepStart()` adds step to active list\n   - Results flow back through channel\n\n3. **Error Handling** (lines 178-193):\n   - If a step returns an error → Run marked `RunStateFailed` immediately\n   - If step returns undeclared result → Run marked `RunStateFailed` immediately\n\n4. **Control Flow via Wiring** (lines 198-225):\n   - Step results are wired to next steps via the `Workflow.NextSteps()` method\n   - Results map to: normal steps, `domain.StepDone` (success terminal), or `domain.StepAbort` (failure terminal)\n   - Each time a target is processed:\n     - If target is `StepDone` → increment `doneCount`\n     - If target is `StepAbort` → set `aborted = true`\n     - Otherwise → launch the target step\n\n5. **Collect Conditions** (lines 227-262):\n   - Collects work similarly but can wait for multiple conditions:\n     - `CollectAll`: all conditions must be satisfied before triggering\n     - `CollectAny`: any condition triggers the target\n\n6. **Final State Determination** (lines 266-274):\n   ```go\n   if aborted || runErr != nil {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   } else if doneCount > 0 {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   } else {\n       run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n       runErr = fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: no branches reached done\", wf.Name)\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Key Insight:** A run succeeds if and only if **at least one branch reaches `domain.StepDone`**. A run fails if:\n- Any step returns an error\n- A step returns an undeclared result\n- The workflow aborts (via `StepAbort`)\n- No branch reaches `StepDone`\n\n### 3. **How \"Attempts\" Work**\n\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 69-134)\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` (line 65)\n\n**Attempt Mechanism:**\n\nAn \"attempt\" is a single execution of an agent step within a retry loop. The system supports `max_attempts` configuration per step:\n\n**Configuration:**\n```\nstep_config[\"max_attempts\"] = \"3\"  // string representation of max retries\n```\n\n**Workflow:**\n\n1. **Check Before Execution** (lines 70-78 in prompt.go):\n   - Before running an agent step, the adapter reads the attempt count from disk\n   - If `count >= max_attempts` → step returns `\"give-up\"` result (special terminal)\n   - This allows workflows to wire give-up to an abort or different path\n\n2. **Increment Counter** (line 79):\n   - `incrementAttemptCount()` writes counter to `.cloche/attempt_count/{stepName}`\n   - Each read/write is to a separate file per step (allows multiple concurrent steps)\n\n3. **Reset on Success** (lines 123-125):\n   - When a step completes with `\"success\"` result → counter is reset to 0\n   - This prevents give-up from triggering after successful fixes whose downstream tests fail unrelated\n   - Pattern: **Attempts only count consecutive failures**\n\n4. **Attempt Counter Implementation** (lines 441-473):\n   - `readAttemptCount()` - reads from `.cloche/attempt_count/{stepName}` (returns 0 if not found)\n   - `incrementAttemptCount()` - creates dir and increments counter\n   - `resetAttemptCount()` - deletes the counter file\n\n5. **Lifecycle** (agent/runner.go line 65):\n   - Entire attempt_count directory is cleared at start of each workflow run\n   - So attempts are tracked per-run, not globally\n\n**Example Workflow Pattern:**\n```\nstep code (agent, max_attempts=3):\n  success → test\n  fail → code (retry)\n  give-up → abort\n```\n\nThis creates an automatic retry loop that gives up after 3 consecutive failures.\n\n### 4. **Existing Tests for Status Computation**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine_test.go`\n\nKey tests include:\n\n1. **TestEngine_LinearWorkflow** (lines 29-50):\n   - Tests simple linear flow: build → test → done\n   - Verifies `RunStateSucceeded` when done is reached\n\n2. **TestEngine_RetryLoop** (lines 52-84):\n   - Tests retry mechanism with:\n     - code (agent) → success/fail\n     - check (script) → pass/fail\n     - fail from check loops back to code\n   - Verifies retry logic and success completion\n\n3. **TestEngine_Abort** (lines 86-105):\n   - Tests abort path: code fail → abort\n   - Verifies `RunStateFailed` when abort is reached\n\n4. **TestEngine_ContextCancellation** (lines 107-128):\n   - Tests context cancellation → `RunStateCancelled`\n\n5. **TestEngine_Fanout** (lines 130-161):\n   - Tests parallel branches all reaching done\n   - Verifies all branches execute\n\n6. **TestEngine_CollectAll** (lines 163-200):\n   - Tests collect waiting for multiple conditions\n   - Verifies merge step only triggers when both test and lint succeed\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go`\n\n1. **TestRun_Lifecycle** (lines 11-31):\n   - Tests state transitions: Pending → Running → Succeeded\n   - Verifies step recording and completion\n\n2. **TestRun_Fail** (lines 54-61):\n   - Tests failure state and error message\n\n### 5. **Additional Status Concepts**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go`\n\nThere's a separate **HealthStatus** concept for project-level health (different from Run state):\n\n- **HealthGreen**: all completed runs in window succeeded\n- **HealthRed**: all completed runs in window failed\n- **HealthYellow**: mix of passed and failed\n- **HealthBlue**: all runs in window are in-progress (pending/running)\n- **HealthGrey**: no runs provided\n\nThis is computed via `CalculateHealth()` (lines 31-76), which takes the most recent N runs and classifies them, independent of run status computation.\n\n### 6. **Status Flow Through the System**\n\n1. **Engine execution** → computes RunState based on step results\n2. **Host executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`, line 217) → maps RunState to step result:\n   - `RunStateSucceeded` → `\"success\"` step result\n   - `RunStateFailed` → `\"fail\"` step result\n3. **Host runner** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, lines 144-154) → persists final state to store\n4. **Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`, lines 197-256) → logs and broadcasts status changes\n5. **Store** (`ports.RunStore`) → persists the Run object with final State\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Run** | Tracks state, step executions, timestamps |\n| **StepExecution** | Records individual step result name |\n| **Engine** | Computes final RunState from step results + wiring |\n| **Attempts** | Per-step consecutive failure counter, resets on success |\n| **Wiring** | Maps (step, result) to next steps or terminals |\n| **StatusHandler** | Logs/broadcasts state changes |\n| **Health** | Aggregates recent runs into project-level status |\n\nThe system design is clean: **Engine is the authority on Run status computation**, while everything else either feeds data to it or consumes its output."}],"totalDurationMs":51083,"totalTokens":63927,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1662,"cache_read_input_tokens":59809,"output_tokens":2456,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1662},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
