[2026-03-13T17:54:42Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B8gtzd7E3PAhdFbSDHDaCG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document for you.\n\n## Summary: Status Command and Attempt Tracking in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here's how the status command works and how attempts relate to step executions:\n\n### 1. **CLI Status Command Handler**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 202-239)\n\nThe `cmdStatus` function:\n- Takes a run ID as argument\n- Calls `client.GetStatus(ctx, &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: args[0]})`\n- Prints formatted output showing:\n  - Run ID, Title, Workflow name, Type (host/container)\n  - State, Container ID, Error message\n  - Active steps (currently running)\n  - All step executions with their results and timestamps\n\n```go\nfor _, exec := range resp.StepExecutions {\n    fmt.Printf(\"  %s: %s (%s -> %s)\\n\", \n        exec.StepName, exec.Result, exec.StartedAt, exec.CompletedAt)\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **gRPC Server Status Handler**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 419-471)\n\nThe `GetStatus` method:\n- Retrieves the run from the store\n- Returns status response containing:\n  - Run metadata (ID, workflow name, state, title, type)\n  - Current active steps (as comma-separated string)\n  - Container liveness status\n  - **Step Executions** from either:\n    - The captures store (if available) - preferred source for detailed tracking\n    - The run's in-memory StepExecutions array (fallback)\n\n```go\nif s.captures != nil {\n    captures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n    if err == nil {\n        for _, exec := range captures {\n            resp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n                StepName:    exec.StepName,\n                Result:      exec.Result,\n                StartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n                CompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n            })\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. **\"Attempts\" Concept - NOT Step Execution Retries**\n**Key Finding**: \"Attempts\" in this codebase are NOT tracking retries of the same step execution shown in status. Instead:\n\n- **Attempts are per-step retry counters** for agent steps with `max_attempts` config\n- **Stored in files**: `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` (contains an integer count)\n- **Purpose**: To prevent infinite retry loops on agent steps\n- **NOT displayed in status output** - they're internal state for workflow control flow\n\n### 4. **Attempt Tracking Mechanism**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 68-79, 441-473)\n\nThe prompt adapter's `Execute` method:\n\n```go\n// Check attempt count for retry limiting\nif maxStr, ok := step.Config[\"max_attempts\"]; ok {\n    max, err := strconv.Atoi(maxStr)\n    if err == nil {\n        count := readAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n        if count >= max {\n            return \"give-up\", nil  // Skip execution, return give-up result\n        }\n    }\n}\nincrementAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n```\n\nHelper functions:\n- `readAttemptCount()` - reads `.cloche/attempt_count/<stepName>` file\n- `incrementAttemptCount()` - increments the counter after each execution\n- `resetAttemptCount()` - clears the counter on success (lines 463-473)\n\n### 5. **How max_attempts Works**\n**Example from DSL**:\n```\nstep fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n**Flow**:\n1. First attempt: count=0 → Execute → increment to 1 → returns result (success/fail)\n2. If failed and wired back to \"fix\": count=1 → Execute → increment to 2 → returns result\n3. If failed again and wired back: count=2 → count >= max → return \"give-up\" WITHOUT executing\n4. If success: reset count to 0 (so downstream failures don't affect future attempts)\n\n### 6. **Step Executions vs. Attempts**\n**Critical Distinction**:\n\n| Aspect | Step Executions | Attempts |\n|--------|-----------------|----------|\n| **What it tracks** | Each time a step runs (regardless of why) | How many times an agent step has been retried |\n| **Stored in** | `Run.StepExecutions[]` array or `step_executions` table | `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` files |\n| **Database column** | Per-execution row with result, start/end times | (Not persisted to DB - file-based only) |\n| **Displayed in status** | YES - all step executions shown with results | NO - not shown in status output |\n| **Why multiple executions** | Normal workflow control flow (fanout, wiring) | Only for retry loops on failed agent steps |\n\n### 7. **Engine/Workflow Execution Model**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe engine does NOT have built-in retry logic. Instead:\n- Launches a step, waits for result\n- Uses wiring to determine next steps based on (step, result) pair\n- If the same step name appears in the wiring again, it launches again (appears as multiple `StepExecution` records)\n- Each execution is tracked as a separate entry in `StepExecutions`\n\nThe retry loop is **entirely in the workflow DSL wiring**, not in the engine:\n```\nstep_1 -> [success] -> done\n          [fail] -> step_1  (creates a wiring loop for retry)\n```\n\n### 8. **Step Execution Recording**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 63-87)\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepStart(stepName string) {\n    r.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps, stepName)\n    r.StepExecutions = append(r.StepExecutions, &StepExecution{\n        StepName:  stepName,\n        StartedAt: time.Now(),\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string) {\n    // Remove from active steps\n    // Mark the most recent execution as complete with the result\n    for i := len(r.StepExecutions) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n        if r.StepExecutions[i].StepName == stepName && r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt.IsZero() {\n            r.StepExecutions[i].Result = result\n            r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt = time.Now()\n            return\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nEach call to `RecordStepStart` creates a NEW `StepExecution` entry, so if a step runs 3 times, there are 3 entries in the array.\n\n### 9. **Database Schema for Attempts**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (line 77)\n\nThe schema includes an `attempt_number` column in `step_executions` table, but it defaults to 0 and is never populated in the current codebase - it's legacy/unused infrastructure.\n\n### 10. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI status command implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | GetStatus RPC handler |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run and StepExecution domain types |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Attempt counting logic (lines 69-79, 441-473) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow engine (no retry logic here) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Database schema and access |\n\n### Summary\n\nThe status command displays all **step executions** (tracked in-memory and persisted to captures store), which represent every time a step actually ran. **Attempts** are a separate concept - file-based counters that prevent agent steps from retrying infinitely when configured with `max_attempts`. Multiple step executions for the same step happen naturally through workflow wiring, not through built-in retry mechanisms."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4605e58752db4e02 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75592\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 35496</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"672a244f-d306-4bfb-8514-5ea42ce22c11","uuid":"72d3f273-8bc7-41a8-902a-c9b09eb0eee8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how the status command works and how step executions relate to \"attempts\" in this codebase. Specifically:\n\n1. Read the CLI status command handler (likely in cmd/cloche/ or internal/adapters/)\n2. Search for any \"Status()\" or \"status\" method on Run that computes a display status\n3. Look for how step executions are grouped by attempts or how the same step might execute multiple times in a retry loop\n4. Search for \"attempt\" in the codebase broadly - look at how attempts are tracked\n5. Read the engine code (internal/engine/engine.go) fully to understand the retry loop mechanics\n6. Look for any status formatting/display code\n\nBe very thorough. Read complete files.","agentId":"a4605e58752db4e02","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document for you.\n\n## Summary: Status Command and Attempt Tracking in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here's how the status command works and how attempts relate to step executions:\n\n### 1. **CLI Status Command Handler**\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 202-239)\n\nThe `cmdStatus` function:\n- Takes a run ID as argument\n- Calls `client.GetStatus(ctx, &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: args[0]})`\n- Prints formatted output showing:\n  - Run ID, Title, Workflow name, Type (host/container)\n  - State, Container ID, Error message\n  - Active steps (currently running)\n  - All step executions with their results and timestamps\n\n```go\nfor _, exec := range resp.StepExecutions {\n    fmt.Printf(\"  %s: %s (%s -> %s)\\n\", \n        exec.StepName, exec.Result, exec.StartedAt, exec.CompletedAt)\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **gRPC Server Status Handler**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 419-471)\n\nThe `GetStatus` method:\n- Retrieves the run from the store\n- Returns status response containing:\n  - Run metadata (ID, workflow name, state, title, type)\n  - Current active steps (as comma-separated string)\n  - Container liveness status\n  - **Step Executions** from either:\n    - The captures store (if available) - preferred source for detailed tracking\n    - The run's in-memory StepExecutions array (fallback)\n\n```go\nif s.captures != nil {\n    captures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n    if err == nil {\n        for _, exec := range captures {\n            resp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n                StepName:    exec.StepName,\n                Result:      exec.Result,\n                StartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n                CompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n            })\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. **\"Attempts\" Concept - NOT Step Execution Retries**\n**Key Finding**: \"Attempts\" in this codebase are NOT tracking retries of the same step execution shown in status. Instead:\n\n- **Attempts are per-step retry counters** for agent steps with `max_attempts` config\n- **Stored in files**: `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` (contains an integer count)\n- **Purpose**: To prevent infinite retry loops on agent steps\n- **NOT displayed in status output** - they're internal state for workflow control flow\n\n### 4. **Attempt Tracking Mechanism**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 68-79, 441-473)\n\nThe prompt adapter's `Execute` method:\n\n```go\n// Check attempt count for retry limiting\nif maxStr, ok := step.Config[\"max_attempts\"]; ok {\n    max, err := strconv.Atoi(maxStr)\n    if err == nil {\n        count := readAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n        if count >= max {\n            return \"give-up\", nil  // Skip execution, return give-up result\n        }\n    }\n}\nincrementAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n```\n\nHelper functions:\n- `readAttemptCount()` - reads `.cloche/attempt_count/<stepName>` file\n- `incrementAttemptCount()` - increments the counter after each execution\n- `resetAttemptCount()` - clears the counter on success (lines 463-473)\n\n### 5. **How max_attempts Works**\n**Example from DSL**:\n```\nstep fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n**Flow**:\n1. First attempt: count=0 → Execute → increment to 1 → returns result (success/fail)\n2. If failed and wired back to \"fix\": count=1 → Execute → increment to 2 → returns result\n3. If failed again and wired back: count=2 → count >= max → return \"give-up\" WITHOUT executing\n4. If success: reset count to 0 (so downstream failures don't affect future attempts)\n\n### 6. **Step Executions vs. Attempts**\n**Critical Distinction**:\n\n| Aspect | Step Executions | Attempts |\n|--------|-----------------|----------|\n| **What it tracks** | Each time a step runs (regardless of why) | How many times an agent step has been retried |\n| **Stored in** | `Run.StepExecutions[]` array or `step_executions` table | `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>` files |\n| **Database column** | Per-execution row with result, start/end times | (Not persisted to DB - file-based only) |\n| **Displayed in status** | YES - all step executions shown with results | NO - not shown in status output |\n| **Why multiple executions** | Normal workflow control flow (fanout, wiring) | Only for retry loops on failed agent steps |\n\n### 7. **Engine/Workflow Execution Model**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe engine does NOT have built-in retry logic. Instead:\n- Launches a step, waits for result\n- Uses wiring to determine next steps based on (step, result) pair\n- If the same step name appears in the wiring again, it launches again (appears as multiple `StepExecution` records)\n- Each execution is tracked as a separate entry in `StepExecutions`\n\nThe retry loop is **entirely in the workflow DSL wiring**, not in the engine:\n```\nstep_1 -> [success] -> done\n          [fail] -> step_1  (creates a wiring loop for retry)\n```\n\n### 8. **Step Execution Recording**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 63-87)\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepStart(stepName string) {\n    r.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps, stepName)\n    r.StepExecutions = append(r.StepExecutions, &StepExecution{\n        StepName:  stepName,\n        StartedAt: time.Now(),\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string) {\n    // Remove from active steps\n    // Mark the most recent execution as complete with the result\n    for i := len(r.StepExecutions) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n        if r.StepExecutions[i].StepName == stepName && r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt.IsZero() {\n            r.StepExecutions[i].Result = result\n            r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt = time.Now()\n            return\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nEach call to `RecordStepStart` creates a NEW `StepExecution` entry, so if a step runs 3 times, there are 3 entries in the array.\n\n### 9. **Database Schema for Attempts**\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (line 77)\n\nThe schema includes an `attempt_number` column in `step_executions` table, but it defaults to 0 and is never populated in the current codebase - it's legacy/unused infrastructure.\n\n### 10. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI status command implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | GetStatus RPC handler |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run and StepExecution domain types |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Attempt counting logic (lines 69-79, 441-473) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow engine (no retry logic here) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Database schema and access |\n\n### Summary\n\nThe status command displays all **step executions** (tracked in-memory and persisted to captures store), which represent every time a step actually ran. **Attempts** are a separate concept - file-based counters that prevent agent steps from retrying infinitely when configured with `max_attempts`. Multiple step executions for the same step happen naturally through workflow wiring, not through built-in retry mechanisms."}],"totalDurationMs":35496,"totalTokens":75592,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4676,"cache_read_input_tokens":68770,"output_tokens":2139,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4676},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
