y: succeeded < cancelled < pending < running < failed)\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:136:- The `task_id` and `task_status` fields are included in the `/api/runs` JSON response\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:148:  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:170:When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:172:which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. Non-success wires within a merge bus\ndocs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md:288:the new step, then wires the new step's results to terminals. This splices the\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:86:The daemon tracks the most recently completed step's output path and passes it to the\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:139:// RunWaiter blocks until the run with the given ID reaches a terminal state.\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:168:6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md:1615:### Task 7: JSON-Lines Status Protocol","numLines":33}}
